Feature: E-Commerce Application Automation Testing

Scenario: Customer Registration
Given User should launch the E-Commerce application
When User should click on the Register link
Then User should enter the First Name
And User should enter the Last Name
And User should enter the Email Address
And User should enter the Mobile Number
And User should enter the Password
And User should click on the Register button
Then User should verify the account is created successfully

Scenario: Customer Login
Given User should open the Login page
When User should enter the registered Email Address
And User should enter the Password
And User should click on the Login button
Then User should verify successful login

Scenario: Product Search
Given User should be logged into the application
When User should enter the product name in the Search box
And User should click on the Search button
Then User should verify that matching products are displayed

Scenario: View Product Details
Given User should have searched for a product
When User should click on the desired product
Then User should verify that the Product Details page is displayed
And User should verify that the product name, description, and price are displayed

Scenario: Add Product to Cart
Given User should be on the Product Details page
When User should click on the Add to Cart button
Then User should verify that the product is added to the shopping cart
And User should verify that the cart count is updated

Scenario: Update Cart
Given User should have products in the shopping cart
When User should update the product quantity
And User should click on the Update Cart button
Then User should verify that the updated quantity is displayed
And User should verify that the total amount is updated

Scenario: Remove Product from Cart
Given User should have products in the shopping cart
When User should click on the Remove button
Then User should verify that the product is removed from the shopping cart
And User should verify that the shopping cart is updated

Scenario: Add Product to Wishlist
Given User should be logged into the application
When User should open the Product Details page
And User should click on the Add to Wishlist button
Then User should verify that the product is added to the wishlist

Scenario: Checkout
Given User should have products in the shopping cart
When User should click on the Proceed to Checkout button
And User should enter the Shipping Address
And User should click on the Continue button
Then User should verify that the Order Summary page is displayed

Scenario: Payment
Given User should be on the Payment page
When User should select the payment method
And User should enter the valid payment details
And User should click on the Pay Now button
Then User should verify that the payment is successful

Scenario: Order Confirmation
Given User should have completed the payment successfully
When User should proceed to the Order Confirmation page
Then User should verify that the Order Confirmation page is displayed
And User should verify that the Order Number is generated
And User should verify that the Order Status is "Confirmed"

Scenario: Order History
Given User should be logged into the application
When User should click on the My Orders option
Then User should verify that all previous orders are displayed

Scenario: Logout
Given User should be logged into the application
When User should click on the Logout button
Then User should verify that the Login page is displayed
And User should verify that the logout is successful